description: The soft-hearted, Kaito takes care of his sick brother and in the end those on his hit-list. During the day, he's a florist, but at night Kaito is an assassin that takes top-secret orders to kill others. The mysterious woman, Sugaru, brings these orders to the flower shop. A hardboiled romance of solitude and shadows, the long awaited first volume filled with love, blood, poison, murder and white lilies. Throughout X-Kai, Kaito faces death through the eyes of his victims.
name: Vol. 1

description: The action continues when Kaito receives his next assignment to assassinate a religious cult leader...but, things turn complicated after he actually joins the cult. Will Kaito be able to eliminate his target once they are face to face?
name: Vol. 2

description: Rika Saginuma's a disenchanted teen--dumped by her boyfriend, off the track team due to an injury - who finds her way into a chat room peopled by 4 similarly disgruntled souls. They meet up at school, exhange contact info, and agree to stay in touch... The 4 kids are all beset by problems that seem to overwhelm them...yet are united by a common fascination: blowing up their school on X-Day...
name: Vol. 1

description: X-Day is fast approaching and all 4 students are looking forward to it with a passion. Rica begins to suspect that all is not right with Kin when she begins noticing bruises, and when she sees his mother abusing Kin, she steps in to protect him and a new love starts to blossom.
name: Vol. 2

description: When an indie Japanese band named Plastic Chew hits it big in Tokyo, will they really have it all? Sure, their dreams have finally come true...but with fame and fortune comes major pressure. Can they be true to their artistic vision while pleasing their management and their fans? Can their relationships with each other hold up under the mounting stress? And, most importantly, can Plastic Chew enjoy success without becoming sellouts? No matter what happens, this band keeps on rockin'...determined to not let anything derail their rock 'n' roll fantasies.
name: Vol. 1

description: Rehearsals at GMB don't produce the results the band had hoped for, and the label's producer Ryan seems to have ulterior motives--and they're not in Plastic Chew's favor. And on top of that, creative differences begin to emerge: Atsushi and Jun want stay true to their original musical style, but Sayuri and Keigo are tempted to go mainstream. Will the band be able to withstand this tug-of-war?
name: Vol. 2

description: A major shake-up is on the horizon for Plastic Chew. Keigo the drummer is being wooed by a major label and is toying with the idea of joining a high profile band. Jun reevaluates his role in the band and what the others bring to the table. And Sayuri is nowhere to be found! Will the band survive all this upheaval? Or do they just need an attitude adjustment? Only time will tell...
name: Vol. 3

description: Meet Plastic Chew, an up-and-coming rock band, desperately in need of a lead singer. Enter Sayuri, a young musician with dreams of rock stardom and a vocal style perfectly suited for PC's sound. Problem is, she's a girl and according to the group's credo--the band that plays together, stays together--living in the same house! Jun, the introverted lead guitarist, isn't at all comfortable with this situation, especially when he finds out Sayuri is a runaway! With a big rock competition fast approaching, will Plastic Chew catch its big break, or break up?
name: Vol. 1

description: Painful, heartbreaking memories suddenly surface for Haru when he agrees to fill in as teacher for the high school archery club. In his youth, Haru was a brilliant archer who competed for the national championship. But uncontrollable urges for a male rival forced him to give up on his rchery dream and run away from his feelings. Now that he's back in the archery game, Haru becomes drawn to the brother of his long-lost love--and he must find out if desire has taken on a new, seductive aim... From Hinako Takanaga, the popular yaoi creator of the boys' love hits Little Butterfly and A Capable Man, comes a tender tale about finding love right in the bull's-eye of one's heart.
name: Vol. 1

description: With Nanako's father on the scene, Grampa is finally motivated to fix the body-switching machine! But now that Akira and Nanako have gotten comfortable in each other's bodies, can things just go back to the way they were? They may have their families to think of, but how can Akira and Senbongi--and Nanako and Shiina--go back to just being friends?
name: Vol. 7

description:
Collected for the first time ever! The original DARKWING DUCK series that fans have demanded! If you love the new DARKWING DUCK original BOOM! comic series, then youll love these classic tales originally published while the show was on the air. That's right all you hardcore D.W. fans out there...here's your chance to rediscover the daring duck of mystery as he gets downright dangerous in his very first comic book escapades, not seen in over a decade! Delight as the Disney Afternoon Revolution takes you on trip down memory lane as Darkwing Duck battles his most famous foes, and learns the ropes of fatherhood all in this 160 page volume!

Back Blurb

He is the terror that flaps in the night!

Collected for the first time ever, join DARKWING DUCK in these classiv adventures not seen in over a decade! Rediscover "the daring duck of mystery" in his very first comic book escapades. Darkwing gets downright dangerous battling his most infamous foes while learning the ropes of fatherhood in this hilarious 160-page volume, only from BOOM! Studios!

Story Titles

  • "Darkly Dawns the Duck." Art & Story: John Blair Moore, Inks: George Wildman
  • "For Whom the Bull Toils!" Art & Story: John Blair Moore, Inks: Gary Martin
  • "Fowl Play!" Art & Story: John Blair Moore, Inks: George Wildman
  • "The End of the Beginning!" Art & Story: John Blair Moore, Inks: George Wildman
  • "Let's Get Fiscal!" Writer: Jim Bricker, Artist: Cosme Quartieri, Inks: Carlos Valenti & Robert Bat
  • "Liquid Diet." Writers: Brian Swenlin & Kevin Campbell, Artist: Chris Allan, Inks: Steve Steere
  • "Turnabout is F.O.W.L. Play" Writer: Doug Gray, Artist: David Schwartz, Inks: Steve Steere
  • "The Found World." Story & Art: John Blaire Moore
name: Darkwing Duck Classics Vol. 1

description: President Obama believes he can finally beat the scandalous Bomb Queen, but our favorite super villain is ready to show the world the TRUE meaning of darkest evil. Don't miss this world-altering conclusion to Bomb Queen vs. Obama where nobody is safe and rivers of blood will flow in the streets.
name: Oh-BOMB-Ah! Final War
